Step-by-Step (Flow Designer)

Go to Flow Designer

Search: Flow Designer

Open it.

Create New Flow

Click New

Name: Send Email on Catalog Item Submit

Click Create.

Select Trigger

Click Add Trigger

Choose: Service Catalog

Then choose: Requested Item

Choose event: Created

Click Done

Add Condition (Optional but useful)
If you want this only for one catalog item:

Click Add Condition

Condition: Catalog Item → is → Your Catalog Item Name

Add Action

Click + Add Action

Select Send Email

Fill Email Details

To: Choose Requested for (from Data Panel)

Data Panel → Requested Item → Requested for → Email

Subject: Write a subject (Ex: Your Request Received)

Body:

Type your email message.

To insert a variable from catalog item:

Right side Data Panel

Expand: Requested Item

Expand: Variables

Click your variable (Example: User_Message)

It will insert something like: {{Requested Item.Variables.User_Message}}

Example Body:

Hello,

Your request has been submitted.
Details: {{Requested Item.Variables.User_Message}}

Thank you.


Save

Click Save (top right)

Turn On Flow

Click Turn On

Testing

Go to Service Catalog

Open Your Catalog Item

Click Order Now

Fill variable value

Submit

Then:
6. Check Email (Requested for user email inbox)

Where to Check Result

Flow Designer → Open your flow → Executions

You will see each run → click → you can see:

Trigger

Variable values

Email details